      },
      "date": "2018-07-14 21:09:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(5 comments)\n\nI think the code looks OK, but the man page can be improved a bit.\n\nIs there a need to allow usage like \"--mirror-index=+2\" or \"! --mirror-id=4\" to allow operations on multiple mirrors at one time?  \nFor example, to change a file to have exactly 2 mirrors you could run \"--mirror-index=+2\" (or +3 if the index starts at 1).  I'm not sure if this is a requirement, but we need to consider how users will use such commands.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
